It's called recursion, where a method calls itself. The function you've defined is for fibonacci series where each number is the sum of the previous 2 numbers in the series such as 0 , 1, 1, 2, 3, 5, 8, 13 and so on. In the given tri_recursion(6) function, it will call tri_recursion(5) which in turn will call tr_recursion(4) until it gets to tri_recursion(0) which returns 0 as given in the if-else. It sounds confusing but is pretty simple. Look up some videos on recursion
